AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1270* House Bill No. 1304
by deleting the language "twenty-five (25)" in subdivision (a)(1)(A) in SECTION 1 and
substituting "fifty (50)".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting "Employee Retirement Income and Security Act of 1974
(ERISA), 29 U.S.C. § 1002(1)" in subdivision (a)(1) in SECTION 1 and substituting "Employee
Retirement Income and Security Act of 1974 (ERISA) (29 U.S.C. § 1002(1))".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting "Public Health Service Act (PHS Act), 42 U.S.C. 300gg–
91(a)(2)" in subdivision (a)(1) in SECTION 1 and substituting "Public Health Service Act (PHS
Act) (42 U.S.C. § 300gg–91(a)(2))".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting "ERISA, 29 U.S.C. § 1002(7)" in subdivision (a)(1)(A) in
SECTION 1 and substituting "ERISA (29 U.S.C. § 1002(7))".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting subsection (c) in SECTION 1 and substituting:
(c) To the extent such information is available to the health benefit plan issuer
and is relevant to the request made under subsection (b), a report provided pursuant to
subsection (b) must include the following information for the thirty-six-month period
preceding the date of the request, for the entire period of coverage, or for the period of
time specified in the request, whichever period is shortest:
(1) Aggregate paid claims experience by month, including claims
experience for medical, dental, and pharmacy benefits, as applicable;
(2) Total premium or premium equivalent earned by month;
(3) Total number of covered employees on a monthly basis by coverage
tier, including whether coverage was for:
